rComments: Prof Campling's lectures were pre-recorded Youtube videos, that were very clear and easy to follow along. Her writing was very neat and she explained concepts very well. Her tests reflected her lectures, so studying was made simple. Thanks for a great first-math-class experience :)

To me she is definitely one of the best professors I have had so far. She really cares to help you if she sees your putting the effort by asking questions when you're confused. Doing the homework helps a lot by the way!

Professor Campling is very knowledgeable about calculus and is always ready to help during office hours. The tests are fair but be careful as they are not out of a lot of marks. Prepare for the tests by looking at the Mobius assignments and suggested exercises.
None of the homework was mandatory, but helped a lot. She was very nice, and available through emails and office hours outside of class. Enjoyed her class!
